                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2637a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-13T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3087. Reports concerning the suffering and increased death rate among German
                    babies owing to milk shortage continue to arouse much sympathy in the United
                    States. Is there any objection to making public Doctor <persName
                        corresp="#p_TDAE1">Taylor</persName>’s report of April 17 transmitted in
                    Embassy’s 2946 of April 18?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
